01:01:31,720 --> 01:01:36,130
And was looking at me,
and talking in their own language.

504
01:01:36,190 --> 01:01:38,860
I understand nothing they're talking about.

505
01:01:38,920 --> 01:01:39,920
Looking at me again.

506
01:01:39,990 --> 01:01:41,370
Laughing and looking and talking.

507
01:01:41,430 --> 01:01:43,130
And I think, "What are they talking about?"

508
01:01:43,190 --> 01:01:44,200
I have no idea.

509
01:02:07,150 --> 01:02:09,030
There was no style.

510
01:02:10,620 --> 01:02:12,290
They're so simple.

511
01:02:12,960 --> 01:02:15,060
They're not creative.

512
01:02:15,130 --> 01:02:17,730
It was the worst team in the league.

513
01:02:17,800 --> 01:02:20,540
Somebody gets open
and they skate away from you.

514
01:02:20,600 --> 01:02:22,600
And you end up on your ass.

515
01:02:22,670 --> 01:02:25,550
They look at you like
you never played before.

516
01:02:27,140 --> 01:02:29,180
Life challenged me all the time.

517
01:02:29,240 --> 01:02:32,450
All of a sudden,
he was drafted by the New Jersey Devils.

518
01:02:47,660 --> 01:02:50,500
Nobody gave a shit about our relationship.

519
01:02:50,560 --> 01:02:52,130
They sign him. We have to play.

520
01:02:52,900 --> 01:02:57,310
It wasn't friendship anymore.
It wasn't team spirit.

521
01:02:57,370 --> 01:02:59,410
It was kind of competition.

522
01:02:59,470 --> 01:03:02,080
It was tough, trust me.

523
01:03:10,780 --> 01:03:13,760
I came to the United States
to play the hockey game.

524
01:03:13,820 --> 01:03:15,960
Not to be involved in this bullshit.

525
01:03:52,990 --> 01:03:56,400
It didn't work out for me,
staying in the NHL.

526
01:03:58,060 --> 01:04:00,770
But that's okay, I think.

527
01:04:00,830 --> 01:04:06,810
All in all, my life worked out.
I think everything's okay.

528
01:04:34,800 --> 01:04:37,810
I was 36.

529
01:04:38,740 --> 01:04:42,480
And they trade me from
New Jersey to Detroit.

530
01:04:45,110 --> 01:04:46,380
<i>Of course..{\i}</i>

531
01:04:46,440 --> 01:04:49,220
<i>We spent so many years
playing and living together.{\i}</i>

532
01:04:49,280 --> 01:04:55,090
<i>You miss the ones you're close to.{\i}</i>

533
01:04:55,450 --> 01:04:58,560
I think, "Oh my God. I did something wrong.

534
01:04:58,620 --> 01:05:01,330
"You've been successful.
You've always been on top.

535
01:05:01,390 --> 01:05:03,630
"Now you're a loser?"

536
01:05:09,970 --> 01:05:15,440
I get out of the dressing room
and see my wife by herself.

537
01:05:15,510 --> 01:05:17,580
Crying.

538
01:05:17,640 --> 01:05:19,420
I said, "Why are you crying?"

539
01:05:19,480 --> 01:05:24,430
She said, "Oh, we got probably
our last chance."

540
01:05:24,480 --> 01:05:27,930
I said, "No."

541
01:05:27,990 --> 01:05:29,590
We've got two choices:

542
01:05:29,650 --> 01:05:31,730
To pack the stuff, go back

543
01:05:31,790 --> 01:05:33,400
or to fight through.

544
01:06:18,870 --> 01:06:24,410
<i>I hereby resign my post
as President of the USSR.{\i}</i>

545
01:06:27,410 --> 01:06:31,760
<i>An end has been put to the
Cold War and the arms race,{\i}</i>

546
01:06:31,820 --> 01:06:34,420
<i>and the mad militarization of this country.{\i}</i>

547
01:06:34,720 --> 01:06:37,790
<i>The threat of nuclear war is over.{\i}</i>

548
01:06:52,100 --> 01:06:55,810
<i>I wish everyone all the best.{\i}</i>

549
01:08:27,400 --> 01:08:29,440
Together again on the same team.

550
01:08:29,500 --> 01:08:32,070
It was like a fish put back in the water.

551
01:08:41,050 --> 01:08:45,520
You become younger right away,
and enjoy the game.

552
01:09:25,320 --> 01:09:27,270
Scotty comes to the dressing room and said,

553
01:09:27,260 --> 01:09:30,330
"Guys, I don't know who teach you
to play this way,

554
01:09:30,390 --> 01:09:33,840
"but I wanna ask you one thing.

555
01:09:33,900 --> 01:09:36,000
"Don't change anything."

556
01:10:30,090 --> 01:10:32,430
I start looking for Igor right away.

557
01:10:32,490 --> 01:10:34,900
And I said, "Igor, we'll go together."

558
01:10:58,650 --> 01:11:01,320
It's true American dream, you know?

559
01:11:06,860 --> 01:11:11,070
Afterwards, I went to Gary Bettman.
I said, "Gary, I need the cup in Moscow."

560
01:11:11,070 --> 01:11:13,610
He said, "You crazy? We'll never
let the cup go to Moscow.

561
01:11:13,660 --> 01:11:16,300
"It's mafia. It's a bad country."

562
01:11:16,370 --> 01:11:19,210
I said, "Listen, I want the cup
to be in Moscow."

563
01:11:21,040 --> 01:11:22,180
He said, "Slava, it's impossible."

564
01:11:22,270 --> 01:11:25,450
I said, "What do you mean impossible?"

565
01:11:31,580 --> 01:11:34,320
<i>it's great to be home.{\i}</i>

566
01:11:34,390 --> 01:11:37,460
<i>For me, the Red Army Club
is home, of course.{\i}</i>

567
01:11:37,520 --> 01:11:40,630
<i>I started here when I was 8 years old,{\i}</i>

568
01:11:40,690 --> 01:11:43,170
<i>and I left when I was 31.{\i}</i>

569
01:11:44,330 --> 01:11:45,810
It's very strange.

570
01:11:45,860 --> 01:11:47,570
When you're born in the Soviet Union,

571
01:11:47,630 --> 01:11:50,940
and you left one country
and come back to another.

572
01:11:52,400 --> 01:11:55,210
It does not feel comfortable, you know?

573
01:11:57,120 --> 01:11:59,850
When I get back to Moscow,

574
01:11:59,910 --> 01:12:02,150
it's totally different.

575
01:12:02,210 --> 01:12:03,690
Different mentality.

576
01:12:03,750 --> 01:12:05,500
Different culture.

577
01:12:05,520 --> 01:12:07,550
Different... Everything's different.

578
01:12:40,720 --> 01:12:42,660
Country's got no heroes. Got no system.

579
01:12:42,720 --> 01:12:45,060
No structure. Nothing.

580
01:12:45,120 --> 01:12:47,190
Everybody runs around
trying to get something.

581
01:12:47,260 --> 01:12:50,860
It's not the way I want to live.

582
01:12:50,840 --> 01:12:54,070
<i>Everything is about the material
side of things: money, finance.{\i}</i>

583
01:12:55,890 --> 01:12:59,040
<i>Our country's crisis
is now reflected in hockey.{\i}</i>

584
01:13:12,570 --> 01:13:18,590
<i>Teams have very little money to
keep players from leaving.{\i}</i>

585
01:13:28,380 --> 01:13:31,710
We kinda forget about the patriotism.

586
01:13:31,770 --> 01:13:34,150
We are ashamed of what we were before.

587
01:13:45,620 --> 01:13:48,100
We lost something.

588
01:13:50,620 --> 01:13:52,970
We lost our pride.

589
01:13:54,960 --> 01:13:56,870
We lost...

590
01:13:56,870 --> 01:13:59,440
Our soul.

591
01:14:14,340 --> 01:14:17,660
Gabe...

592
01:14:17,710 --> 01:14:20,320
It's not a proper question.

593
01:14:20,380 --> 01:14:21,970
I'm a politician now.

594
01:14:21,970 --> 01:14:25,960
I get my feeling twenty years ago, right?

595
01:14:26,020 --> 01:14:27,590
I was sad.

596
01:14:27,660 --> 01:14:29,730
I played for the country for many years.

597
01:14:29,790 --> 01:14:32,730
I was proud to play and
be captain of the national team.

598
01:14:36,630 --> 01:14:40,270
When Putin invited me it was 2002.

599
01:14:40,340 --> 01:14:43,950
It's 11 years it's no Soviet Union.

600
01:14:45,740 --> 01:14:48,280
President Putin said, "Slava, it's enough.

601
01:14:48,910 --> 01:14:51,620
"Get back home."

602
01:15:01,330 --> 01:15:04,330
Vladimir Putin gave me the position
of Minister of Sport.

603
01:15:07,140 --> 01:15:09,480
Sport should be a way of life.

604
01:15:14,000 --> 01:15:18,010
I'm a little guy in a big system,
but I try to do my best.

605
01:15:42,570 --> 01:15:45,340
It's a huge amount of work.

606
01:15:45,400 --> 01:15:48,850
It's twenty hours working day. Every day.

607
01:15:54,650 --> 01:15:56,780
Y'know, we got lots of problems.

608
01:15:56,850 --> 01:15:58,550
I need to build infrastructure.

609
01:15:58,620 --> 01:15:59,820
I need to find the money.

610
01:15:59,820 --> 01:16:02,870
I need to think about my people now.

611
01:16:02,850 --> 01:16:04,830
The kids, the veterans...

612
01:16:04,890 --> 01:16:08,730
Try to build something good
out of what's happened.

613
01:16:11,900 --> 01:16:14,500
We built a junior league.

614
01:16:15,000 --> 01:16:18,720
We built 300 new skating arenas.

615
01:16:20,140 --> 01:16:24,720
We brought the Olympic Games to Sochi.

616
01:16:33,450 --> 01:16:35,690
We are happy to be back in our country.

617
01:16:37,350 --> 01:16:40,300
I think our country and people need us.

618
01:16:55,010 --> 01:16:56,920
We went through a lot,

619
01:16:56,920 --> 01:17:00,170
and I'm happy today we are
again like brothers.

620
01:17:00,170 --> 01:17:02,520
Very close friends.

621
01:17:04,250 --> 01:17:06,750
We're friends.

622
01:17:06,820 --> 01:17:12,730
It's very important to get the people
you went through a lot with next to you.

623
01:17:13,140 --> 01:17:15,610
It's better than finding somebody else.

624
01:17:19,460 --> 01:17:21,570
We're still friends.

625
01:17:21,570 --> 01:17:23,450
And when we played, we were even closer.

626
01:17:25,300 --> 01:17:29,160
I dream about how we used to play together.

627
01:18:14,480 --> 01:18:19,330
<i>First, a round of applause for this great
Soviet coach.{\i}</i>

628
01:18:19,820 --> 01:18:23,900
<i>The word "great" hardly begins to describe
this great coach!{\i}</i>

629
01:18:23,960 --> 01:18:28,100
<i>Unfortunately, Viktor says
he's unable to talk today.{\i}</i>

630
01:18:47,650 --> 01:18:49,760
The most important thing for me

631
01:18:49,820 --> 01:18:53,030
is to stress to the kids how it's
important to be teammates.

632
01:18:53,090 --> 01:18:55,160
How important to do stuff collectively.

633
01:18:55,230 --> 01:18:58,500
To be proud of what team you play on.

634
01:19:29,030 --> 01:19:31,230
I played 23 professional years.

635
01:19:32,460 --> 01:19:36,470
One thousand eight hundred plus games.

636
01:19:37,530 --> 01:19:43,380
I never had fun more than
playing with those five guys, together.

